<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7887499>
    dc:description "Fig. 26. Scanning electron micrographs for Diognetus cheimon sp. nov.from Nagasaki, Japan,J (AÔłĺK) andÔÖÇ (LÔłĺP).AÔłĺB ÔÇô left lateral habitus; C Ôłĺ pleura and scent efferent system, left lateral view; D Ôłĺ head and pronotum, left lateral view; D Ôłĺ anterior body, left lateral view; E Ôłĺ metatarsus; FÔłĺG Ôłĺ pretarsal structure of metaleg; H Ôłĺ apex of pygophore with exposed vesica and left paramere; I Ôłĺ right paramere; J Ôłĺ left paramere; K Ôłĺ vesica (endosoma); L Ôłĺ sclerotized ring; M Ôłĺ apex of ovipositor (gonapophysis I); N Ôłĺ posterior wall; O Ôłĺ dorsal structure; P Ôłĺ interramal lobe." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation <https://zenodo.org/record/7887499/files/figure.png> ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7887519>
    dc:description "Fig. 36. Scanning electron micrographs for Diognetus yamato Yasunaga nom. nov. from Shikoku, Japan (AÔłĺI), J (AÔłĺF) and ÔÖÇ (GÔłĺI), and immature forms of D. cheimon sp. nov. from Nagasaki, Japan (JÔłĺL), D. styrax sp. nov. from Nantou, Taiwan (MÔłĺN) and D. vernus sp. nov. from Nagasaki (O). A Ôłĺ anterior body, left lateral view; B Ôłĺ apex of labium with mandibular and maxillary stylets; C Ôłĺ pleura and scent efferent system, left lateral view; D Ôłĺ metatarsus; E, L Ôłĺ pretarsal structure of metaleg; F Ôłĺ apex of pygophore with parameres, left lateral view; G Ôłĺ posterior wall; H Ôłĺ dorsal structure and interramal lobe; I Ôłĺ apex of ovipositor (gonapophysis I); J Ôłĺ 5th instar exuvia, right lateral view; K Ôłĺ 5th instar thorax and abdomen, dorsal view; M Ôłĺ 5th instar nymph, anterior body; N Ôłĺ same, dorsal habitus; O Ôłĺ 5th instar exuvia, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation <https://zenodo.org/record/7887519/files/figure.png> ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7887423>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Habitats and host plants, Japan (AÔłĺF), Nepal (GÔłĺH) and Taiwan (I) for Diognetus cheimon sp. nov. (AÔłĺF), D. laureus sp. nov. (AÔłĺF), D. vernus sp. nov. (AÔłĺF), D. bagmaticus sp. nov. (G), D. puspae sp. nov. (H) and D. styrax sp. nov. (I). AÔÇôC Ôłĺ Eurya emarginata at preserved wetland (A), house entrance (B) and seaside park (C) in Nagasaki; D Ôłĺ Machilus thunbergii at Satoyama zone in Nagasaki City; EÔłĺF Ôłĺ Castanopsis sieboldii at coastal zones in Nagasaki City; G Ôłĺ Quercus semecaprifolia, inflorescence, at Nagarjun, Kathmandu; H Ôłĺ flowers of Schima wallichii at Godawari Valley, Lalitpur; I Ôłĺ Styrax formosanus, flowers, in Nantou." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation <https://zenodo.org/record/7887423/files/figure.png> ;
    a fabio:Figure .

